<!--
IL2CPP AOT stripping can remove metadata that System.Text.Json's reflection-based
JsonSerializer.Deserialize<T> needs at runtime, since none of the calls in
UnityStreamingAssetsDataSource use source-generated (de)serialization. This has never been
exercised under IL2CPP before (Windows Standalone uses Mono), so preserve TowerOfChrome.Core
wholesale rather than risk a silent MissingMethodException on an Android device. If this proves
insufficient, the fallback is a source-generated JsonSerializerContext (see
docs/android-porting-notes.md).
-->
<linker>
  <assembly fullname="TowerOfChrome.Core" preserve="all" />
</linker>
